      ],
      "summary": "Ehsaas Foundation Inc is a humanitarian organization dedicated to the <cite id=\"1\">relief of poverty and assisting the poor</cite> during times of crisis. The organization operates a diverse range of programs including <cite id=\"2\">Ramadan appeals, food distribution, and water projects</cite> to address immediate survival needs. In the 2023 fiscal year, the foundation reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $1,324,818</cite>, which was primarily derived from public contributions. Despite a <cite id=\"4\">3-year revenue CAGR of -17.4%</cite>, indicating a recent contraction in funding, the organization maintains a <cite id=\"5\">program expense ratio of 87.8%</cite> according to its financial profile. This high ratio suggests that a significant majority of donor funds are directed toward direct service delivery rather than administrative overhead. Furthermore, the organization demonstrates <cite id=\"6\">exceptional fundraising efficiency</cite>, spending $0.00 to raise every $1. Operations are geographically focused on vulnerable populations in <cite id=\"7\">Pakistan, India, and the Philippines</cite>, providing culturally sensitive aid such as <cite id=\"8\">Qurbani services and masjid construction</cite>.",
